div.div: Kyoukai no Kanata: I'LL BE HERE - Mirai-hen
Action, Drama, Fantasy, Romance, Slice of Life, Supernatural
This is the second part of a two-part movie. The story takes place one year after the TV series.
Action, Drama, Mecha, Psychological, Romance, Sci-Fi

Tokyo 2039, Japan has fallen under the control of the multinational organization GHQ after the outbreak, in 2029, of an epidemic caused by a virus known as Apocalypse.
Shuu Ouma, wielder of "The Power of Kings", has led a rather secluded life at least until his encounter with Gai Tsusugami and Yuzuriha Inori, members of the resistance, thrusts him into the fight against the GHQ.

Although Yuji Itadori looks like your average teenager, his immense physical strength is something to behold! Every sports club wants him to join, but Itadori would rather hang out with the school outcasts in the Occult Research Club. One day, the club manages to get their hands on a sealed cursed object. Little do they know the terror they’ll unleash when they break the seal… (Source: Viz Media) Note: Ranked 1st in Japan's Bookstore Employees Top Manga of 2018. Nominated to the 25th Annual Tezuka Osamu Cultural Prize.
Comedy, Romance, Slice of Life, Sports

After moving out on his own to a seaside town, Iori Kitahara makes a college debut he never anticipated. A new chapter of his life unfolds, full of diving with beautiful girls and shenanigans with a gaggle of lovable bastards! Idiot-expert Kenji Inoue and au naturel authority Kimitake Yoshioka bring you a glorious college tale filled with booze-fueled antics! (Source: Kodansha USA)
